INSERT INTO `categories` VALUES (12,NULL,1,'Medical','medical','2019-07-09 08:44:48','2019-07-09 08:44:48','',NULL,NULL,'',0,NULL),(13,NULL,1,'Cosmetic','cosmetic','2019-07-09 08:47:12','2019-07-09 08:47:12','',NULL,NULL,'',0,NULL),(15,12,1,'Orthopedics','orthopedics','2019-07-09 08:56:42','2019-11-25 08:43:15','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#What-is-Orthopedics\">What is Orthopedics?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Orthopedic-surgery-in-Iran\">Orthopedic surgery in Iran</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"What-is-Orthopedics\" class=\"template-subtitle\">What is Orthopedics?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Orthopedics</strong> (also spelled <strong>Orthopaedics</strong>), is one of medicine&rsquo;s subspecialties focusing on the musculoskeletal system (an organ system that enables the human to move). <strong>Orthopedic surgeons</strong> can use both non-surgical and surgical methods to treat different conditions. Common <strong>Orthopedic procedures</strong> include:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><a href=\"https://medtouriran.com/en/packages/19/knee-replacement-surgery\"><strong>Knee replacement surgery</strong></a>: <strong>Knee replacement</strong> (also called <strong>Knee arthroplasty</strong>) is an <strong>Orthopedic</strong> procedure aimed to treat a damaged knee and replacing the knee joint with an artificial one.&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Hip replacement surgery</strong>: Hip replacement (also called Hip arthroplasty) is a procedure that involves removing a painful hip joint with arthritis and replacing it with an artificial joint. This procedure is usually done when other treatments have failed.</li>\n<li><strong>Ankle replacement surgery</strong>: Ankle replacement (also called Ankle arthroplasty) involves removing a damaged ankle joint and replacing it with an artificial one. This surgery enables you to move your ankle freely and without pain.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://medtouriran.com/en/packages/22/shoulder-replacement-surgery\"><strong>Shoulder replacement surgery</strong></a>: Shoulder replacement surgery (also called total shoulder arthroplasty) aims to relieve pain and improve mobility by removing damaged areas of the shoulder and replacing them with artificial ones. This procedure is needed when you have severe arthritis or a fracture in the shoulder joint.</li>\n<li><strong>Meniscus repair</strong> : Menisci is a C-shaped disc of soft tissue (called cartilage) that connects the thigh bone to the shinbone and helps keep the knee stable. Meniscus repair is an arthroscopic surgery done to repair torn knee cartilage. Athletes are prone to meniscus tears.</li>\n<li><strong>Achilles tendon repair</strong>: The Achilles tendon is the largest tendon in the body which connects the heel bones to the calf muscles. Achilles tendon is a springy band of tissue at the back of your ankle and above the heel. Achilles tendon repair surgery fixes a damaged Achilles tendon.</li>\n<li><strong>Herniated disc surgery</strong>: There are discs between the bones in the spine acting as shock absorbers. If the annulus within the spine is ruptured, a part of the disc nuclus will be pushed out of the annulus into the spinal canal. This condition is called a herniated disc. Lifting something wrong and suddenly twisting the spine can cause a&nbsp; herniated disc. This condition is not painful unless the disc pushes against a nerve. Herniated disc surgery is usually done when other treatments have failed.</li>\n<li><strong>Laminectomy</strong> : Laminectomy surgery (also called Decompression surgery) is performed to create space by removing the lamina (back part of a vertebra which covers the spinal canal). Laminectomy relieves pressure on the spinal nerves. This surgery is usually done when other treatments are unsuccesfull or the symptoms are severe.</li>\n<li><strong>Spinal fusion</strong>: Spinal fusion (also called Spondylodesis) is done to join two or more vertebrae (small bones in the spine). Spinal fusion is analogous to welding process.</li>\n<li><strong>PCL reconstruction surgery</strong> : To replace a torn Posterior cruciate ligament (PCL), the patient should undergo PCL reconstruction surgery. This surgery involves replacing the torn PCL with your own tissues or an allograft.</li>\n<li><strong>Scoliosis surgery</strong>: The presence of an abnormal curve in the spine is called scoliosis. To fix this abnormal curve, Scoliosis surgery is recommended. If the curve is bigger than 45-50 degrees, Scoliosis surgery is needed.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"Orthopedic-surgery-in-Iran\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Orthopedic surgery in Iran</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Iran is among the top 10 countries in <strong>Orthopedics. </strong>Iranian&nbsp;surgeons perform high-quality surgeries at affordable prices. Iran is also a great country to travel to due to its rich culture and history, warm-hearted people, and exquisite cuisine. Many people from various countries travel to Iran yearly to get different surgeries. If you have decided to travel to Iran for your <strong>Orthopedics </strong>surgery, you can contact <strong>MedtourIran</strong> any time to get consultation and plan your trip.</p>\n</div>','categories/August2019/I2NdBQQUqzEEjRn8Dbfi.jpg',NULL,'Orthopedics (also spelled Orthopaedics), is one of medicine’s subspecialties focusing on the musculoskeletal system (an organ system that enables the human to move). Orthopedic surgeons can use both non-surgical and surgical methods to treat different conditions. ',1,'categories/August2019/thWakDgmGFOmzMfLUPl2.jpg'),(17,12,1,'Cardiology','cardiology','2019-07-09 09:10:51','2019-11-25 09:00:14','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#Cardiology\">Cardiology</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Angioplasty\">Angioplasty</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Open-Heart-Surgery\">Open-Heart Surgery</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Catheter-Ablation\">Catheter Ablation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Heart-Valve-Surgery\">Heart Valve Surgery</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Echocardiography\">Echocardiography</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Aortic-Surgery\">Aortic Surgery</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"Cardiology\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Cardiology</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Cardiology</strong> is one of the subspecialties of medicine, focusing on heart disorders and the circulatory system (cardiovascular system). <strong>Cardiologists</strong> are physicians who have specialized in <strong>Cardiology. Cardiology </strong>includes procedures such as:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Angioplasty</li>\n<li>Open Heart Surgery (Coronary Artery Bypass Graft or CABG)</li>\n<li>Catheter Ablation</li>\n<li>Heart Valve Surgery</li>\n<li>Echocardiography</li>\n<li>Aortic Surgery</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"Angioplasty\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Angioplasty</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Angioplasty</strong> is also known as <strong>balloon angioplasty</strong> or <strong>coronary</strong> <strong>angioplasty</strong>. <strong>Angioplasty</strong> is performed to widen or open clogged heart veins. In this surgery a balloon catheter is inserted into the narrowed or clogged vein. Then the balloon is inflated into a specified size which forces the vein to expand and improves blood flow. To make sure that the vein stays open, a stent (a metal or plastic tube) might be inserted into the vein and finally, the balloon is withdrawn.</p>\n<h3 id=\"Open-Heart-Surgery\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Open-Heart Surgery</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">The most common type of heart surgery performed on adults is the <strong>Open-Heart Surgery</strong> or <strong>CABG</strong> (coronary artery bypass surgery). This surgery is done when the patient\'s blood veins have become narrow and hard, which is called coronary heart disease. This surgery is also done to repair damaged areas of the heart or to repair or replace heart valves.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"Catheter-Ablation\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Catheter Ablation</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Catheter Ablation</strong> is also called <strong>Radiofrequency</strong> <strong>Ablation</strong>. This procedure uses radiofrequency waves to treat arrhythmias. Radiofrequency waves are used to destroy small areas of the heart tissue causing irregular heartbeats. <strong>Catheter Ablation</strong> is performed when medication is not effective. <strong>Radiofrequency Ablation</strong> is also a safe and effective method to deal with some forms of pain.</p>\n<h3 id=\"Heart-Valve-Surgery\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Heart Valve Surgery</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">There are four valves in the heart, each with different names. In case one of these valves doesn&rsquo;t function properly, <strong>Heart Valve Surgery</strong> is needed. During the surgery, based on the patient\'s condition, the surgeon can either repair or replace the heart valves. <strong>Heart Valve Surgery</strong> can be performed through using different surgical procedure like <strong>open-heart surgery</strong> or minimally invasive heart surgery.</p>\n<h3 id=\"Echocardiography\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Echocardiography</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Echocardiography</strong> is also known as a <strong>Cardiac Echo</strong> or simply an <strong>Echo </strong>. <strong>Echocardiography</strong> creates images of the heart via using ultrasound. This method is one of the most widely used diagnostic tests in <strong>cardiology</strong>. A heart <strong>Echo</strong> provides lots of helpful information like the shape or the size of the heart and enables doctors to completely monitor the heart.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"Aortic-Surgery\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Aortic Surgery</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">The aorta is the main blood vessel which carries blood from the heart to the rest of the body. If the aorta somehow becomes weak, the pressure of the blood flow can cause it to swell. This condition is called \'aneurysm\'. If the aneurysm is small, it can be treated with medicine, but larger ones need surgery. Most aortic disorders are treated by using open surgical repair.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>','categories/August2019/eUJig8aWoTsQftPNe0B9.jpg',NULL,'Cardiology is one of medicine’s subspecialties, focusing on heart disorders and the circulatory system (cardiovascular system). Cardiologists are physicians who specialize in this field. ',1,'categories/August2019/GH32TRghvglBAinsMIkn.png'),(19,12,1,'Ear, Nose and Throat','ear-nose-and-throat ','2019-07-09 09:12:04','2019-11-25 09:16:29','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">What is ENT?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a2\">Head and Neck Surgery</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a3\">Otology &amp; Neurotology</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a4\">Rhinology</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a5\">Laryngology</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a6\">Pediatrics</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a7\">Tonsillectomy</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a1\" class=\"template-subtitle\">What is ENT?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Otorhinolaryngology</strong> is one of the surgical subspecialties of medicine, focusing on ear, nose, and throat conditions. Simply put, this field is commonly known as <strong>ENT</strong> (Ear, Nose, and Throat) and doctors who specialize in this field are called <strong>Otorhinolaryngologists</strong> or <strong>ENT doctors</strong>. Some of the subspecialties of <strong>ENT </strong>are:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Head and Neck Surgery</li>\n<li>Otology &amp; Neurotology</li>\n<li>Rhinology</li>\n<li>Laryngology</li>\n<li>Pediatrics</li>\n<li>Thyroid and Parathyroid Surgery (the surgical treatment of thyroid and parathyroid tumors)</li>\n<li>Facial Plastic Surgery</li>\n<li>Tonsillectomy</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a2\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Head and Neck Surgery</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">This subspecialty includes surgeries such as:&nbsp;</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li><strong>Parotidectomy. </strong>This surgical operation is done to remove the parotid gland (the biggest salivary gland). <strong>Parotidectomy</strong> is needed when there are tumors in the parotid gland. These tumors can either be benign (non-cancerous) or malignant (cancerous).</li>\n<li><strong>Neck Dissection</strong>. If cancer cells migrate to the lymph nodes located on the sides of the neck, a <strong>neck dissection</strong> is needed. During this operation, the lymph nodes are removed.</li>\n<li><strong>Laryngectomy</strong>. This surgery is done to remove the larynx (voice box).</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a3\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Otology &amp; Neurotology</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Otology</strong> is one of the branches of medicine which focuses on the ears, their anatomy, conditions, and treatments. <strong>Neurotolgy</strong> or <strong>neuro-otology</strong> is one of the sub-specialties of <strong>ENT,</strong> which studies the neurological conditions of the ear and how to treat them. <strong>Otology</strong> deals with conditions such as:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Hearing loss</li>\n<li>Chronic ear infections</li>\n<li>Cholesteatoma</li>\n<li>Otosclerosis</li>\n<li>Acoustic neuroma</li>\n<li>Cochlear implants</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a4\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Rhinology</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">&nbsp;Rhinologists are doctors who have specialized in nose and sinus problems. <strong>Rhinology</strong> involves treating nasal polyps, chronic sinusitis and many other conditions. <strong>Rhinology</strong> includes procedures such as:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li><a href=\"https://medtouriran.com/en/procedures/43/rhinoplasty\">Rhinoplasty</a></li>\n<li>Septoplasty</li>\n<li>Turbinate surgery</li>\n<li>Endoscopic sinus surgery</li>\n<li>Nasal polyp removal</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Rhinologists can work closely with ophthalmologists (eye doctors) to perform &lsquo;endoscopic orbital surgeries&rsquo;. Endoscopic orbital surgeries are done to treat conditions like &lsquo;persistent tearing&rsquo;. Rhinologists can also team up with neurosurgeons to treat nasal and skull base conditions like &lsquo;skull base tumors&rsquo; or &lsquo;nasal and sinus tumors&rsquo;.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a5\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Laryngology</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Larynx is commonly known as &lsquo;the voice box&rsquo; and <strong>Laryngology</strong> is focused on treating voice disorders, airway and swallowing problems, and laryngeal (throat) cancer. <strong>Laryngology</strong> is a very inclusive specialty. Laryngologists deal with conditions like:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Dysphagia (difficulty in swallowing)</li>\n<li>Dysphonia (difficulty in speaking)</li>\n<li>Thyroplasty (which is done to improve the voice)</li>\n<li>Tracheostomy (which is done to allow air to enter the lungs)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The above-mentioned procedures are just few of the many procedures that <strong>laryngology</strong> includes.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a6\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Pediatrics</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Pediatrics</strong> is focused on taking care of infants, children, and adolescents. Sleep apnea and glue ear are two of the conditions that pediatricians deal with.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a7\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Tonsillectomy</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">There are two oval-shaped tissue pads at the back of throat, called tonsils. <strong>Tonsillectomy</strong> is the surgical procedure to remove the tonsils in case they become infected or swollen.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">&nbsp;</p>\n</div>','categories/August2019/fEKhwZBS6s0XkdQM1g8s.jpg',NULL,'Otorhinolaryngology is one of medicine’s surgical subspecialties, focusing on ear, nose, and throat conditions. To make things easier it’s called ENT (Ear, Nose, and Throat) and doctors who specialize in this field are called Otorhinolaryngologists or ENT doctors. Head and neck structures are also included in this field. Some of ENT’s subspecialties are:',0,'categories/August2019/TSagZtDipjArmqdByFqx.jpg'),(20,12,1,'Eye Care','eye-care','2019-07-09 09:12:52','2019-11-25 08:24:36','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">What is Eye Care?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a2\">Common Types of Eye Surgery</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a3\">Why Iran?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a4\">Precautions</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a5\">Complications </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a6\">Eye Exam</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a1\" class=\"template-subtitle\">What is Eye Care?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">The eye is a very important and fragile organ in your body and needs extreme care. There are a number of vision disorders such as myopia (near-sightedness), hyperopia (far-sightedness) and astigmatism that are included among refractive errors. That is why everyone needs to have regular checkups to diagnose the possible errors in his/her eyes through the eye exam and take action to resolve them by using eyeglasses, contact lenses or having surgery.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a2\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Common Types of Eye Surgery</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Today, eye surgery has improved in various ways and can be used for treating eye problems. Laser eye surgery is a common solution that can correct short-sightedness, long-sightedness, and astigmatism by reshaping the surface of the eye.</p>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">LASIK (laser-assisted in situ keratomileusis) is a laser vision correction method that can improve your vision by changing the shape of your cornea and is similar to LASEK. The chances of having dry eyes after the surgery are reduced in Lasek. However, the time needed for recovery is longer in contrast to LASIK. You must consult with an experienced ophthalmologist to choose the best option according to your eye condition.</p>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Cataract is an eye condition that usually happens with aging and is mostly seen among the elderly. Due to the cloudiness of the eye&rsquo;s lens, a cataract cannot be corrected with glasses or LASIK. In this case, modern cataract surgery is used, which is a common eye surgery and often can restore your vision. Various types of eye surgery are available for the patients and it is an expert eye surgeon responsibility to propose the best procedure suitable for you.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a3\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Why Iran?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">There are a number of&nbsp; problems related to how a patient heals after the operation, which make choosing an experienced surgeon to be considered an important factor in this process. That being said Iran has:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Very well-educated and highly-experienced surgeons and ophthalmologists that can help the patients to have their desired vision after the eye surgery.</li>\n<li>Well-equipped clinics and hospitals using advanced technologies for eye treatments.</li>\n<li>Affordable prices</li>\n<li>High quality and high success rate of eye treatments</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">If you seek treating eye disease abroad and you&rsquo;ve chosen Iran to have your surgery, Medtouriran can provide you with ophthalmic treatments by using the latest techniques at affordable prices. Furthermore, you can go sightseeing and visit the historical and natural attractions of the capital city, Tehran, while you&rsquo;re in the city.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a4\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Precautions</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">There are a number of things you need to do before and after the eye surgery, which are more or less the same in different types of eye surgeries. If you are planning to get LASIK (in particular), remember to:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Remove all makeup the night before surgery</li>\n<li>Stop wearing soft contacts before surgery. Ask your surgeon to give you more details about how long before the Lasik surgery you need to stop wearing them.</li>\n<li>Ask someone to drive you back home after the surgery</li>\n<li>If you take specific medication, consult with your surgeon to see if you&rsquo;re allowed to continue taking them before or after the eye surgery.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a5\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Complications</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">There are some myths about Lasik that you might have heard of. For instance, some people believe that you can go blind from Lasik surgery;&nbsp; that&rsquo;s not true and such a thing has never happened to anyone. However, there are some temporary side effects:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Dry eyes</li>\n<li>Glare</li>\n<li>Night vision problems</li>\n<li>Seeing halos around images</li>\n<li>Not getting the expected results (over- or under-correction)</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Taking the necessary safety precautions can reduce the side effects of eye surgery. Moreover, there are some treatment options that can help you manage these problems successfully.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a6\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Eye Exam</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Just as it is important to take care of your body, you also need to get your eyes checked regularly to diagnose possible eye diseases and start the proper treatment as soon as possible. So, take care of your eye seriously and don&rsquo;t postpone your appointment with your ophthalmologist.</p>\n</div>','categories/August2019/v1PswqmvTfXDDeHQ1ofv.jpg',NULL,'The eye is a very important and fragile organ in your body and needs extreme care. There are a number of vision disorders such as myopia (near-sightedness), hyperopia (far-sightedness) and astigmatism that are included among refractive errors. That is why everyone needs to have regular checkups to diagnose the possible errors in their eyes through the eye exam and take action to resolve them by using eyeglasses, contact lenses or having surgery.',1,'categories/August2019/vyKmcdoSgLrQI3U7hlrI.jpg'),(22,12,1,'Female Fertility','female-fertility','2019-07-09 09:57:11','2019-11-25 09:59:22','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">What is Infertility?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a2\">Infertility symptoms</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a3\">Common Causes of Infertility</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a4\">Infertility Treatment</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a5\">Why Iran?</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a1\" class=\"template-subtitle\">What is Infertility?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Having a baby and becoming a parent is one of the most beautiful and life-changing events that you can experience in your life. Most women are able to conceive a child within one year of trying and it is more likely to get a positive result during the earlier months. Some others (approximately 7%) can have a baby in the second year. That is why it is said that if you have been trying to get pregnant within 12 months but you couldn&rsquo;t, you&rsquo;d better see a doctor and make sure that everything is okay.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a2\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Infertility symptoms</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">If you are diagnosed with <strong>Infertility</strong> (inability to conceive a child), you can get treatment. But first let&rsquo;s take a look at some of the symptoms that can help you to seek help earlier:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li><strong>Irregular menstrual periods: </strong>One of the signs which shows that a woman ovulates regularly is having regular menstrual periods (every 21 to 35 days). Ovulation of the egg is necessary for pregnancy. Therefore, if you&rsquo;re trying to conceive a baby and you have irregular menstrual cycles, do not wait until the 12th month, take action and see a doctor to find out the problem.</li>\n<li><strong>Women over 35: </strong>As women age, they are faceed with reduction in the number of eggs and it is less likely for an egg to be genetically normal. Accordingly, if a woman has been trying to have a baby for 6 months or more and the woman is over 35 years old, they&rsquo;d better be evaluated for <strong>infertility.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>&nbsp;A history of sexually transmitted diseases: </strong>A sperm must cross the tubes in order to reach the ovulated egg and fertilize it. Therefore, open tubes are essential to get pregnant naturally. Sexually transmitted diseases such as gonorrhea, can damage fallopian tubes and prevent a proper conception. That is why if a woman has a history of pelvic infection, she should get an immediate evaluation if she intends to conceive a child.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a3\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Common Causes of Infertility</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Delaying childbirth:</strong> As discussed previously, the number of eggs will diminish as a woman ages. A woman beyond the age of 45 is unlikely to get pregnant.</li>\n<li><strong>Endometrial polyps:</strong> Endometrial polyps can arise from the inner lining of the uterus and can decrease fertility. In some cases, if the doctor simply removes the polyp, your <strong>infertility</strong> will be solved.</li>\n<li><strong>&nbsp;Male factor infertility:</strong> If the abnormality of semen is confirmed, the man should visit a reproductive urologist to get proper treatment.</li>\n<li><strong>Uterine fibroids:</strong> Fibroids are very common among women and have three types. Submucosal fibroids are the type that can reduce the chance of pregnancy and need to be treated so that the couple can have a baby.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a4\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Infertility Treatment</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Couples need to educate themselves about the symptoms of <strong>infertility</strong> so that they know when to seek help. Aside from that, your doctor can suggest special treatments to help you conceive a child:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li><strong>Medications:</strong> In order to stimulate egg development and ovulation, your doctor may prescribe special pills or injections. You should use them as you&rsquo;re instructed to enhance the chance of conceiving a baby.</li>\n<li><strong>Insemination:</strong> Insemination is a method in which they take the sperm and prepare it for placement into the uterine cavity. In this case, there is a probable chance for the sperm to get closer to the ovulated egg. The man needs to be checked for sperm abnormality, otherwise, the sperm cannot swim and fertilize the egg.&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>In Vitro Fertilization:</strong> IVF means &ldquo;outside the body&rdquo; and the reason is that in this process, doctors collect eggs and fertilize them by sperm outside the body, in the laboratory. They check the eggs again after about 40 hours and if they are fertilized, they will be put back in the woman\'s uterus.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a5\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Why Choose Iran for Infertility Treatment?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Aside from affordable prices for <strong>infertility treatment</strong> in Iran (compared to other countries), there are a number of other reasons that you&rsquo;d better consider visiting this country to find the best treatment awaiting you:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Advanced treatment for <strong>infertility</strong></li>\n<li>Knowledgeable and experienced specialists</li>\n<li>Well-equipped hospitals and laboratories</li>\n<li>Beautiful attractions to visit while you are in the city</li>\n</ul>\n</div>','categories/August2019/TFGLIGOHDBDmlPcq0JVs.jpg',NULL,'Having a baby and becoming a parent is one of the most beautiful and life-changing events that you can experience in your life. Most couples can conceive a child within one year of trying and it is more likely to get a result during the earlier months. Some others (approximately 7%) can have a baby in the second year. That is why it is said that if you have been trying to get pregnant within 12 months but you couldn’t, you’d better see a doctor and make sure that everything is okay.',1,'categories/August2019/WniEPPiZGF1mTIp5wwTl.jpg'),(34,13,1,'Ear  Surgery','Ear-surgery','2019-07-09 10:17:12','2019-11-25 11:32:40','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">What is Pinnaplasty?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a2\">Otoplasty Risks and Side Effects</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a3\">Different Otoplasty Types</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a4\">Otoplasty Procedure</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a5\">Non-surgical Otopalsty</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a6\">Good Candidates for Otoplasty</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a7\">Otoplasty Preparation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a8\">Otoplasty Recovery</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a9\">Why Choose Iran for Your Otoplasty?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a10\">Otoplasty Costs</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a1\" class=\"template-subtitle\">What is Pinnaplasty?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">The outer ear is called &lsquo;pinna&rsquo; and <strong>Pinnaplasty</strong> is the surgical procedure which corrects the pinna in case it is prominent or if it has any deformities. This procedure is also known as <strong>Otoplasty</strong> or cosmetic ear surgery. This procedure does not affect hearing because hearing involves the middle and inner ear, but <strong>Otoplasty</strong> is focused on the outer ear. This procedure involves reshaping or repositioning the ears to make them less prominent and more natural. Keep in mind that prominent ears don&rsquo;t count as a medical condition however, having this surgery might help you feel more confident.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a2\" class=\"template-subtitle\"><strong>Otoplasty Risks</strong> and Side Effects</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Just like any other major surgeries, <strong>Otoplasty</strong> has various risks like infection, bleeding, anesthesia risks, asymmetrical ears, scarring. <strong>Otoplasty</strong> can also cause changes in skin sensation or create an unnatural look, making the ears look pinned back.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a3\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Different Otoplasty Types</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Otoplasty</strong> has three different types:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li><strong>Ear Pinning: </strong>Ear pinning is also called <strong>Otopexy</strong> and is done to flatten prominent ears.&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Ear augmentation: </strong>If the pinna is underdeveloped, the condition is called microtia. <strong>Ear augmentation</strong> is aimed to treat this condition by reconstructing or enlarging the pinna.&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Ear Reduction: </strong>If the pinna is larger than normal, the condition is called macrotia. <strong>Ear reduction surgery</strong>&nbsp;reduces the size of abnormally large ears by removing cartilage and skin from the ears.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a4\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Otoplasty Procedure</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Otoplasty</strong> is usually done under general anesthesia which means that you will be unconscious during the surgery. Depending on the patient&rsquo;s condition, the surgeon can either make incisions on the back of the ears or within the inner creases of the ears. After the incisions are made, your surgeon will make changes to the ear depending on the condition. At the end, the head will be wrapped with bandages to protect the ears. <strong>Otoplasty</strong> procedure takes a couple of hours.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a5\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Non-surgical Otopalsty</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">The traditional <strong>Otoplasty</strong> involves making incisions and removing excess skin and cartilage however, there is an alternative. <strong>Non-surgical Otoplasty</strong> is performed using only stiches to pin the ears back. These stiches are permanent but not visible or tangible. The upside to this method is that patients can instantly see the results and if they are not satisfied by them, the procedure can be reversed a few days after the initial surgery. <strong>Non-surgical Otoplasty</strong> is done using local anesthesia and you can return to your daily activities within a few days.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a6\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Good Candidates for Otoplasty</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">The ears reach 80% of their adult size by the age of 6. Traditional <strong>Otoplasty</strong> can be performed on patients who are at least 4 years old but <strong>Non-surgical Otoplasty</strong> is more suitable for patients older than 6. During the first two weeks after birth, in case the infant has prominent ears, ear molds can be used to correct the ears since the cartilage is still soft.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a7\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Otoplasty Preparation</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Before the surgery you need to talk to your surgeon. During the consultation your surgeon will:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Review your medical history</li>\n<li>Examine your ears</li>\n<li>Take photographs for comparison</li>\n<li>Talk about your expectations</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Also before having surgery you need to avoid taking certain medication like aspirin because they may cause bleeding. You should also stop smoking before the surgery because it slows the healing process and increases the risk of infection. You should also arrange for someone from <strong>MedtourIran</strong> to take you home after the surgery and stay with you for at least one night.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a8\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Otoplasty Recovery</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">After the surgery, your ears will be covered with bandages for support and protection. The bandages will be removed after 7-10 days. When the bandages are off, you should wear a headband for 2-6 weeks while sleeping in order to keep the ears pinned back. It is natural if your ears feel sore. If you have severe pain or if there is bleeding, you should immediately contact your doctor. You should also keep your ears clean to minimize the risk of infection. Although your ears might feel itchy, you should not touch or rub them otherwise, you damage the sutures. If you are not satisfied with the results, you should talk to your doctor about a revision surgery.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a9\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Why Choose Iran for Otoplasty?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">The surgeons in Iran are well-educated and highly experienced. Hospitals and clinics in Iran are advanced and very well equipped. Almost any surgery in Iran costs less than any other country, but the difference in the costs doesn&rsquo;t mean that the quality of the services is low. This difference is basically based on economic factors. Hospitable and kind people, exquisite cuisine, beautiful and breathtaking historical attractions are just few of the many reasons why you should consider Iran as your destination. If you have chosen Iran for your surgery, you can contact <strong>MedtourIran</strong> to get consultation and plan your trip.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a10\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Otoplasty Costs</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Otoplasty</strong> costs vary widely. <strong>Otoplasty</strong> in Iran costs between 1000$ and 2200$, but if you want to have this surgery in the US it will cost you around 3150$. The cost of <strong>Otoplasty</strong> starts from 1500$ in India, and the average cost of it in Turkey is 2200$. If you want to have this surgery in European countries, the average cost is about 2000$. So it is more reasonable to have this surgery in Iran because you will get the same quality of services at lower and more affordable prices.</p>\n</div>','categories/August2019/mIUWxdwFBIrzkzIj0v9k.jpg',NULL,'The outer ear is called ‘pinna’ and Pinnaplasty is the surgical procedure which corrects the pinna in case it is prominent or if it has any deformities. This procedure is also known as Otoplasty or cosmetic ear surgery. This procedure does not affect hearing because hearing involves the middle and inner ear but Otoplasty is focused on the outer ear. This procedure involves reshaping or repositioning the ears to make them less prominent and more natural. Keep in mind that prominent ears don’t count as a medical condition however, having this surgery might help you feel more confident. ',0,'categories/August2019/25UutuXe9FUN36HpeBHH.png'),(35,13,1,'Eyelids surgery','eyelids-surgery','2019-07-09 10:17:24','2019-11-25 12:19:19','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">What is Blepharoplasty?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a2\">Is Blepharoplasty Dangerous?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a3\">When is Blepharoplasty Needed?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a4\">Blepharoplasty Procedure</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a5\">Non-surgical Blepharoplasty</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a6\">Recovery from Blepharoplasty</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a7\">Blepharoplasty in Iran</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a1\" class=\"template-subtitle\">What is Blepharoplasty?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">As you age, your eyelids stretch therefor, excessive fat may gather below or above the eyelids causing droopy upper lids and bags under the eyes. Sagging skin around your eyes can make you look older and even reduce your peripheral vision. <strong>Blepharoplasty,</strong>&nbsp;also known as an <strong>eye lift</strong> or <strong>eyelid surgery</strong>, is a cosmetic eye surgery operation that reduces bagginess from lower eyelids and removes excessive skin from the upper eyelids. <strong>Blepharoplasty</strong> also can improve vision problems and make your eyes look younger. Keep in mind that <strong>blepharoplasty</strong> doesn&rsquo;t change the form of the eyes but will help you have a more refreshed and younger look.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a2\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Is Blepharoplasty Dangerous?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">It&rsquo;s completely normal for the eyelids to swell and bruise after the operation. The surface of the eyeball may also swell. These symptoms will subside after 1 or 2 weeks. For almost 2 weeks your eyes might feel dry and could be treated with eye drops or ointments. It&rsquo;s natural if your sight is a little blurry for a few weeks. If the eyelids become sensitive and red, it&rsquo;s probabely the wound is opened and may become infectious and spread to the whole eyelid. If this happens, contact the hospital immediately so that the doctors can control the infection by antibiotics. Bleeding after the <strong>blepharoplasty</strong> operation is often very little and will stop after a short while. If the bleeding continues, contact the hospital immediately to get treatment because severe bleeding around or behind the eye can damage the vision but it&rsquo;s very rare. In another rare case, during the operation too much skin is removed and the patient has trouble closing the eye, in this case the skin must be replaced to correct it or in case any excessive skin remains another surgery must be done.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a3\" class=\"template-subtitle\">When is Blepharoplasty Needed?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Usually people get their eyelids lifted for one of these reasons:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>To treat the bags under their eyes</li>\n<li>Droopy and saggy eyelids</li>\n<li>Excessive skin or wrinkles under their eyes</li>\n<li>Their eyelids make them look older</li>\n<li>To improve their vision</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a4\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Blepharoplasty Procedure</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Blepharoplasty</strong> is done under either general or local anesthesia. Depending on the patient, it can be done on the upper or lower eyelids or both. <strong>Blepharoplasty</strong> procedure includes the steps:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>The incision</li>\n<li>Removing excessive skin, removing\\relocating fat and muscle</li>\n<li>Tightening muscles</li>\n<li>Closing the incision</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If the incisions are made using a laser, the procedure is called \'<strong>laser blepharoplasty</strong>\' which reduces the risk of scarring. This method is less painful and bruises less but causes more swelling.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a5\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Non-surgical Blepharoplasty</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Non-surgical blepharoplasty</strong> or <strong>plasma therapy</strong> uses PlexR. PlexR is a device that forms plasma to sublimate the excess skin. Its energy is delivered only to superficial skin cells without affecting deeper tissues. This method is also called <strong>dynamic blepharoplasty</strong> because during the procedure the patients are asked to open\\close their eyes to enable the doctor detect the wrinkles that need to be treated it also enables patients to follow the procedure. This method almost has no side effects and according to surveys all of the patients are fully satisfied with the results.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a6\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Recovery from Blepharoplasty</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">At the end of the eyelid surgery, ointments will be applied on the incisions and the stitches. Your eyelids may have pain and feel stretched which is usually mild and will become better by using ordinary painkillers. Contact your doctor if you have severe pain or if your vision is reduced. Using cold compresses for a few days after the surgery will help control the bruising and the swelling. Usually the eyes are most swelled within the first week but the swelling will subside after 2-4 weeks. During the first weeks after the operation, sensitivity to light and transient visual changes such as blurry sight may occur but will pass gradually. In the first 2-3 weeks you need to get checked by the doctor frequently. The stitches are usually removed after 4-7 days after the operation and after the stitches are removed you will look better. Most people will be able to read books or watch TV after 1-2 days. In general, until 2-3 weeks after the operation contact lenses can&rsquo;t be used, and up to 4 weeks after the operation the eyes are very sensitive to sunshine, wind, and dust and it is better to use big sunglasses and sunscreen. You should limit your activities for the first 4-5 days after the surgery and rest as much as possible.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a7\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Blepharoplasty in Iran</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">After rhinoplasty, <strong>blepharoplasty</strong> is the most common cosmetic surgery in Iran. Iran enjoys highly experienced surgeons and modern clinics and hospitals. Compared to other countries, the proceedures are more affordable in Iran, as a result Iran is a very good option for <strong>blepharoplasty</strong> or other cosmetic surgeries. If you have chosen Iran for your <strong>blepharoplasty,</strong> you can ask for help from <strong>MedTourIran</strong> specialists.</p>\n</div>','categories/August2019/Uiei6sv8YPxWqxDsOBVK.jpg',NULL,'من اثار التقدم في العمر تجمع الدهون تحت الجفون أو فوقها مما ينتج عن هذا الهدل في العيون أو بتعبير آخر تصبح لديك عيون متدلية ذات ترهلات تجعلك تبدو اكبر سنا. تقوم هذة العملية بإزالة جميع الدهون و الجلود الزائدة من الجفون و حول العيون. كما تساعد العملية على تقليل مشاكل الرؤية وتجعل عينك تبدو أصغر سنا. \nالجدير بالذكر أن عملية جراحة العيون التجميلية تساعد على مظهر أجمل و منتعش و لا يحدث تغيير لشكل العيون.\n',0,'categories/August2019/xRudn8WhEFKaCSUdFlNZ.jpg'),(43,13,1,'Rhinoplasty','rhinoplasty','2019-07-09 10:19:42','2019-11-25 13:03:09','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">What is Rhinoplasty?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a2\">Types of Rhinoplasty</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a3\">Rhinoplasty in Iran</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a4\">Best Age For a Nose Job</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a5\">Risks of Rhinoplasty</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a6\">Rhinoplasty Preparations</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a7\">Non-surgical Rhinoplasty</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a8\">Different Nose Types </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a9\">Common Rhinoplasty Styles</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a10\">Recovery from Rhinoplasty</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a1\" class=\"template-subtitle\">What is Rhinoplasty?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Rhinoplasty,</strong>&nbsp;also known as a \'<strong>nose job</strong>\' is a plastic surgery aimed to make people improve their appearance. Rhinoplasty might have medical reasons as well. A <strong>nose job</strong> can be accompanied by other plastic surgery operations such as blepharoplasty (eyelid surgery) or genioplasty (chin surgery) to enhance the result. <strong>Rhinoplasty</strong> has become very common among peoples of all nations (especially Iran).</p>\n<h3 id=\"a2\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Types of Rhinoplasty</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Rhinoplasty generally can be divided into 2 categories of \"aesthetic rhinoplasty\" and \"functional rhinoplasty\":</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li><strong>Aesthetic rhinoplasty</strong> has cosmetic reasons and the patients usually intend to change the appearance of their nose so that it will be in better harmony with other parts of their face and to generally suit their face more. Note that your health insurance might not cover cosmetic surgeries.</li>\n<li><strong>Functional rhinoplasty</strong> can be done for medical problems; for instance, to improve breathing or correct congenital defects.</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<p>We can also put a nose surgery into 2 groups of primary and secondary or revision rhinoplasty.</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Primary rhinoplasty. If it is the first time that you are having rhinoplasty, it\'s called primary rhinoplasty; whether it\'s aesthetic or functional.</li>\n<li>Secondary rhinoplasty indicates that you have already gotten a nose job, but it wasn\'t successful (which is not that common) and you need to reshape your nose due to problems like asymmetry, pinched tip, etc. That\'s why it is also called a revision rhinoplasty. The latter usually involves a more difficult procedure since the surgeon must recreate the nasal support that was probably destroyed in the primary rhinoplasty.</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a3\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Rhinoplasty in Iran</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Rhinoplasty</strong> is the most common cosmetic surgery in Iran. Iran is known as \'the nose job capital of the world\' and there must be a good reason for that. We might be able to say that nose surgery has become a part of a fashion trend these days and the main reason that nose surgery has become very popular among Iranians is their Persian nose. Most Persia people prefer the European nose and this factor results in increasing rate of nose surgery in Iran. In recent years, people from all over the world, especially the Middle East, have shown a special interest in flocking to Iran for their <strong>nose job</strong>. The cause of this high demand can be traced to the following reasons:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>The high-quality plastic surgery that patients experience in Iran plays an important role in this matter.</li>\n<li>Surgeon\'s experience is important in predicting success rates. Iranian surgeons are well-educated and highly-experienced in this nose job and this is not surprising because of&nbsp; the number of people they deal with every day.</li>\n<li>High levels of clinical care is another reason for the popularity of <strong>rhinoplasty</strong> in Iran.</li>\n<li>You can do the operation in the capital city of Iran, Tehran, and its other big towns such as Mashhad, Shiraz, Isfahan, etc. Therefore, aside from dealing with medical issues, you can also take a tour of these historical towns and visit their top attractions while you are in the city.</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a4\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Best Age for a Nose Job</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">If you have a medical reason for getting surgery, a <strong>nose job</strong> can be done at younger ages; However, if you solely want to get a <strong>nose job</strong> to look better and improve your appearance, the proper age for girls is about age 15 and a bit older for boys.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a5\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Risks of Rhinoplasty</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">No surgery is risk-free and <strong>rhinoplasty</strong> is no exception. <strong>Rhinoplasty</strong> can cause:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>A numb nose</li>\n<li>Breathing difficulties</li>\n<li>Bleeding</li>\n<li>Infection</li>\n<li>Dissatisfaction with the final resault</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">If you are not satisfied with your nose after the operation, you might want a second surgery which can be done, but in this case, you should wait until your nose is fully healed (maybe a year) and then get prepared for the second operation.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a6\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Rhinoplasty Preparations</h3>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>First, you meet with a surgeon and discuss the details about your medical conditions, if getting a <strong>nose job</strong> is a good choice for you then, you decide on how you want your nose look loke after the surgery.</li>\n<li>Your surgeon will closely examine the skin inside and outside your nose and might ask you to get a blood test.</li>\n<li>In addition to that, they might take pictures of your nose from various angles to be used during the surgery or to make comparisons or assess the results after a while.</li>\n<li>Remember not to take medicines or painkillers (before or after the operation) without consulting your surgeon.</li>\n<li>A <strong>nose job</strong> can be done in a hospital or a doctor\'s office.</li>\n<li>You&rsquo;ll either be unconscious during the surgery or your surgeon will numb your face, but generally you\'ll stay awake.</li>\n<li>Finally, the operation and reshaping of your nose start and it take 1 to 2 hours or even longer if the procedure is more complex.</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a7\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Non-surgical Rhinoplasty</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Surgeons can non-surgically reshape the nose with dermal fillers and make improvements that will last up to a year. A skilled surgeon can smooth out bumps, reshape the nose&rsquo;s tip and improve its symmetry. It is important to keep in mind that the results are temporary but many unnecessary <strong>rhinoplasty</strong> operations can be avoided using this cost-effective approach and avoid extra expenses and side effects. You can also use this method to test out a nose reshaping before committing to the permanent changes.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a8\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Nose types</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Noses can be divided into two categories: bony noses and meaty ones. The difference between these two types is in the thickness of the skin. Meaty noses have thicker skin. In the <strong>rhinoplasty</strong> of a bony nose small changes will have significant results.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a9\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Common Rhinoplasty Styles</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">There are three types of nose jobs: a natural nose job, a fantasy nose job and a semi-fantasy nose job. Usually meaty noses get natural nose jobs where smaller changes are applied. Those who have small faces are more suitable for a fantasy nose job which results in a small and upturned nose.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a10\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Recovery from Rhinoplasty</h3>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>You will return home and it\'s necessary to follow your doctor\'s instructions.</li>\n<li>Get enough rest and let the bone tissues heal after being cut.</li>\n<li>Your surgeon might prescribe medications to alleviate pain.</li>\n<li>It usually takes one week before you can go outside and the bruising around your eyes will heal in the second week.</li>\n<li>If the surgeon hasn\'t used dissolvable stitches, you\'ll need to see your doctor again a week after surgery to get the stitches taken out.</li>\n<li>Your doctor will inform you to avoid running, swimming, laughing, wearing eyeglasses or blowing your nose.</li>\n<li>Above all, you need to avoid sun exposure as the skin around your nose is more prone to sun damage after the surgery.</li>\n<li>You can also use cold compresses after the operation to decrease swelling.</li>\n<li>Finally remember that it can take a whole year before you can see the final result of the surgery. So don\'t be so quick to judge your new nose and give it enough time to fully recover and become a normal nose again.</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">If you\'re considering <strong>rhinoplasty</strong> and you\'ve chosen to do it in Iran, you can always ask for help from <strong>MedTourIran</strong> specialists and consult a surgeon to decide what is best for you.</p>\n</div>','categories/September2019/DmwtwPfawGpCkUKJsA41.jpg',NULL,'Rhinoplasty which is also referred to as a nose job is a kind of plastic surgery that can be done to help the patients feel better about their appearance or it might have medical reasons. A nose job can be accompanied by other plastic surgery operations such as blepharoplasty (eyelid surgery) or genioplasty (chin surgery) to enhance the result. Rhinoplasty has become very common among peoples of all nations (especially Iran).',1,'categories/September2019/f4m7WjiWCTrIiCZKcCFS.jpg'),(50,13,1,'Hair transplant','hair-transplant','2019-07-30 23:44:31','2019-11-25 13:14:50','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">What is Hair Transplant?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a2\">Hair Transplant Procedure</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a3\">Why Choose Iran?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a4\">Are You The Right Candidate for a Hair Transplant?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a5\">Hair Transplant Risks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a6\">Hair Transplant Results</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a1\" class=\"template-subtitle\">What is Hair Transplant?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Hair has a significant impact on your appearance. Due to this impact, many people suffering from hair loss are looking for a permanent solution to stop this process once and for all. Today, surgeons can deal with hair loss by transplanting healthy hairs into the balding part of the body. This procedure is called <strong>hair transplant</strong> and usually is not done all of a sudden; meaning that hairs will be implanted over time. This process gives the hair a natural look compared to the <strong>hair transplantation</strong> in the 70s and 80s.</p>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Back then, it was quite noticeable, and people could quickly notice if someone&rsquo;s hair was not natural. Today, thanks to the advances in this area, people (maybe not even your barber) can hardly tell the difference. <strong>Hair transplant</strong> is the most common cosmetic surgery procedure performed on men since they usually tend to go bald sooner. Hair loss isn&rsquo;t specific to men, and women can also experience it at any age.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a2\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Hair Transplant Procedure</h3>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li><strong>Hair transplant</strong> is generally safe and can take between 4 to 8 hours.</li>\n<li>Usually, the dermatologist only uses local anesthesia which makes the scalp numb, but you will remain awake during the entire surgery.</li>\n<li>As we mentioned before, the surgeon will remove healthy hairs, and place them in the thinning areas.</li>\n<li>When the transplantation is finished, the surgeon will bandage your scalp, and give you the necessary instructions to follow at home.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a3\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Why Choose Iran?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">In a <strong>hair transplant</strong> procedure, a correct distance, angle, and density play an important role in getting a natural outcome. In general, the result of your <strong>hair transplant</strong> depends a lot on the surgeon you choose. This is why many people select Iran for their surgery. Other reasons that make Iran a perfect destination for a <strong>hair transplant</strong> include:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Experienced surgeons</li>\n<li>Affordable costs of <strong>hair transplant</strong> in Iran (compared to other countries)</li>\n<li>Its exceptional and incomparable attractions</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a4\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Are You The Right Candidate for a Hair Transplant?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Regardless of your gender or the cause of your hair loss (heredity, medical problems, etc.), you can be a good candidate for a <strong>hair transplant</strong> if:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>There is enough healthy hair on your scalp for the surgeon to use and transfer to the thinning areas.</li>\n<li>The balding areas should have the capacity to grow hair on them.</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Your dermatologist will carefully examine your scalp and inform you if you have both conditions. Your doctor may also ask you to take a blood test to find out the cause of your hair loss. According to the results of the tests and exams, the dermatologist can almost tell you what to expect after the <strong>hair transplant</strong>. Expecting a full head of hair is quite unrealistic, but your hair and the balding areas will surely look better and fuller after the <strong>hair transplant</strong>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a5\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Hair Transplant Risks</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Hair transplant</strong> should be done in a hospital setting to decrease the possible risks. Hair transplant includes risks such as:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Infection</li>\n<li>Swelling</li>\n<li>Bruising</li>\n<li>Itching</li>\n<li>Scarring</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you choose an experienced plastic surgeon for your<strong> hair transplant</strong>, complications are less likely to happen. Any other problems like bruising or numbness in the balding areas of your head will subside within 2-3 months after the surgery.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a6\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Hair Transplant Results</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Usually, patients can see results between 2 and 8 months after the <strong>hair transplant, but</strong>&nbsp;it might take almost 12 months for some people. Moreover, it is completely normal for the transplanted hair to fall out between 2 and 8 weeks after the surgery (shock loss) and grow again later. So, don&rsquo;t panic!</p>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Also, by the third month, your hair may look thinner compared to the way it looked before the <strong>hair transplantation</strong>. Again, don&rsquo;t worry and be patient. Your dermatologist might prescribe medication to aid your hair loss and help you keep your natural-looking results.</p>\n</div>','categories/August2019/tvGDbf4YSdAPJSCi15U7.jpg',NULL,'Hair has a huge impact on your appearance and that’s why many people who deal with hair loss are looking for a permanent solution to stop this process once and for all. Today, surgeons can do this by transplanting the healthy hairs into the balding part of the body. This procedure is called hair transplant and usually is not done all of a sudden; meaning that a few hairs at a time is taken and will be implanted to areas of hair loss. This process gives the hair a natural look compared to the hair transplantation in 70s and 80s.',1,'categories/August2019/zDQLSbBAtfbtxxQRtoTt.jpg'),(51,12,1,'dental health','dental-health','2019-08-04 05:44:17','2019-11-25 11:03:42','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">What is Dental Health?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a2\">Oral Hygiene Habits</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a3\">Why Choose Iran?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a4\">Oral Diseases</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a5\">Treating Dental Problems</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a1\" class=\"template-subtitle\">What is Dental Health?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">You might not notice, but your <strong>dental health</strong> (aka oral health) says a lot about your overall health status. Several oral hygiene habits can prevent oral problems such as tooth decay, bad breath, dry mouth, etc.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a2\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Oral Hygiene Habits</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Poor oral hygiene has negative effects on your health, yet it is usually taken for granted. <strong>Dental treatment</strong> is costly. Therefore, it is much less troublesome to take care of your teeth before it\'s too late. If you are experiencing dental pain, don\'t put off seeing a dentist. Also, try following these oral hygiene habits to keep your teeth healthy and reduce oral diseases:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Brush your teeth twice a day (with a fluoride toothpaste)</li>\n<li>Don\'t forget flossing</li>\n<li>Limit your sugar intake</li>\n<li>Have a well-balanced diet</li>\n<li>Schedule regular dental check-ups</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a3\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Why Choose Iran?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">You might want to consider Iran as your dental tourism destination due to the following reasons:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Affordable prices (the same procedures will cost much higher in the US)</li>\n<li>Highly-experienced dentists</li>\n<li>Well-equipped clinics</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Hospitality of Iranians which is usually considered to be the best part of traveling to Iran</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a4\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Oral Diseases</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">You need to take care of your teeth, otherwise, facing one of the dental problems mentioned below is certain. Just consider how many times you use your mouth and teeth every day for eating different kinds of things.&nbsp;</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li><strong>Tooth Decay: Cavities,</strong>&nbsp;also known as <strong>Tooth Decay,</strong> are parts of the teeth that are damaged and may even have holes in them. As a result, your teeth will be sensitive when you have a hot, cold, or sweet drink. One way to decrease the number of bacteria and plaque in your mouth is to brush and floss your teeth regularly.</li>\n<li><strong>Gingivitis: Gingivitis</strong> or <strong>Gum Diseases</strong> happen due to poor oral hygiene habits. In this disease, your gums become red and swollen and may bleed when you brush your teeth.&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Periodontitis: </strong>If you don\'t treat <strong>gingivitis,</strong> it may lead to <strong>Periodontitis</strong>, which is more serious.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a5\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Treating Dental Problems</h3>\n<p><strong>Dental health</strong> is related to the overall health of your body and can help you maintain a healthy body. Oral bacteria can lead to heart disease, premature birth, etc. Therefore, it is necessary to treat oral diseases as early as possible. Also, there are many things you can do to make your teeth look better. Here are short descriptions of the most important ones.&nbsp;</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li><strong>Braces and Retainers: </strong>If your teeth are crooked and you want a nice-looking smile, an orthodontist can straighten your teeth using braces and retainers.&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Teeth Whitening: </strong>Teeth Whitening can lighten the natural color of your teeth. There are some teeth whitening methods you can use at home like using whitening toothpaste. But for more professional methods you\'d better let the dentist do the job.&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Cleanings:</strong> It is harder to reach some parts in your mouth, and some tartar or plaque might remain on your teeth during brushing or flossing. Cleaning can remove any debris remaining between your teeth.&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Fillings and Crowns:</strong> If you have a hole, crack or cavity in your tooth, you can repair the damage with a filling. The dentist will use a crown to fill in the gap where a large portion of your teeth has broken off and needs to be removed. In most cases, this process can resolve your problem, but in some rare cases with extreme overbite or underbite, surgery might be a better solution.&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Dental implants: </strong>If you have lost a tooth in an accident or any other occasions, an implant can be used to replace the lost tooth by placing it into the jawbone. Then, a crown which suits your other teeth will be added to give it a more natural look.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>','categories/August2019/5jKp7o62Xd6DmgS6YJOo.jpg',NULL,'You might not notice, but your dental health (aks oral health) says a lot about your overall health status. There are a number of oral hygiene habits that can prevent oral problems such as tooth decay, bad breath, dry mouth, etc.',0,'categories/August2019/QajEC8LiGMLxz0AH3knn.jpeg'),(52,13,1,'Liposuction','liposuction','2019-08-04 05:49:35','2019-11-25 13:24:55','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">Liposuction Defenition</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a2\">Risks and Side Effects</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">Liposuction </a><a href=\"#a3\">Types</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a4\">Preparations</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a5\">Recovery</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">Liposuction </a><a href=\"#a6\">Cost</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a8\">Good Candidates for Liposuction</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a1\" class=\"template-subtitle\">What is Liposuction?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Lipo means fat and <strong>Liposuction</strong> is a cosmetic surgery in which fat is removed from certain areas of the body. <strong>Liposuction</strong> will help you get rid of fat that you haven&rsquo;t been able to get rid of with diet or exercise. However, keep in mind that this surgery won&rsquo;t help you get rid of cellulite. Also, <strong>Liposuction</strong> shouldn&rsquo;t be considered a solution for weight loss. <strong>Lipoplasty</strong> is a Liposuction technique in which ultrasonic waves are used to liquefy the fat under the skin before removing it. This method makes the fat easier to remove, so <strong>Ultrasonic-Assisted Lipoplasty</strong> (UAL) is an enhancement to Liposuction. <strong>Liposuction</strong> is used to remove fat from areas such as:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Abdomen</li>\n<li>Buttocks</li>\n<li>Hips and thighs</li>\n<li>Chin and neck</li>\n<li>Breasts</li>\n</ul>\n<div id=\"template-images\" class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\n<div class=\"theme-img template-image\"><img alt=\"\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<h3 id=\"a2\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Risks and Side Effects of Liposuction</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Just like any other surgery, <strong>Liposuction</strong> also has risks such as:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Infection, which is rare</li>\n<li>Bleeding</li>\n<li>Anesthesia risks</li>\n<li>Fluid accumulation</li>\n<li>Numbness</li>\n<li>Blood clots</li>\n<li>Fat embolism</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">If fat is removed unevenly, or due to skin&rsquo;s poor elasticity, the skin can become bumpy, which may be everlasting.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a3\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Different Liposuction Types</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Based on your preference, the areas treated and your <strong>Liposuction</strong> will be done using different techniques. Different <strong>Liposuction</strong> types are:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Tumescent Liposuction (the most common type)</li>\n<li>Ultrasound-Assisted Liposuction (UAL) also known as <strong>Lipoplasty</strong></li>\n<li>Laser-Assisted Liposuction (LAL)</li>\n<li>Power-Assisted Liposuction (PAL)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a4\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Liposuction Preparations</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Before the surgery, your surgeon might ask you to stop taking certain medications. You should discuss your expectations with your surgeon and ask any questions you have. Your surgeon will check your medical history and might take photos to use for comparison. If you are not having a lot of fat removed, you might not need a hospital stay and should arrange for someone to drive you home after the surgery.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a5\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Recovering from Liposuction</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">You&rsquo;re likely to experience pain, swelling, and bruising after the surgery. Your surgeon may prescribe painkillers, and antibiotics to reduce the risk of infection. The swelling usually subsides within a few weeks, and after a few months, the treated areas will have a leaner appearance. You can return to your daily activities within two weeks. <strong>Liposuction</strong> results will generally last as long as you maintain your weight, but if you gain weight, your body&rsquo;s fat distribution may change.</p>\n<h3 id=\"6\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Liposuction cost</h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a6\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Liposuction Alternatives</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Liposuction</strong> has a less invasive alternative called <strong>Non-Surgical Fat Reduction</strong> or <strong>Non-Surgical Liposuction</strong>. <strong>Liposuction</strong> involves a small incision and sucking out the fat through a tube. <strong>Non-Surgical Fat Reduction</strong> uses heat, lasers, cooling, or sound waves to destroy fat cells and melt the fat away. <strong>Non-Surgical Liposuction</strong> almost has no recovery time but can&rsquo;t affect large areas of fat. This method should be used when the patient doesn&rsquo;t want to undergo surgery. Another alternative for <strong>Liposuction</strong> is <strong>water-assisted body sculpting</strong> known as <strong>body jet</strong> which uses pressurized water streams to wash out the fat.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a7\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Liposuction in Iran</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Liposuction</strong> is among the top five cosmetic surgeries done in Iran, and the cost of this surgery in Iran is considerably lower than in other countries. Iran enjoys highly educated and highly experienced surgeons, modern clinics and hospitals, and offers high-quality medical services. Iran is also a great country to travel to due to its rich culture and history, hospitable people, amazing architecture and much more. So when it comes to undergoing surgery at a considerably lower price but with the same quality, Iran can be an excellent choice. If you&rsquo;re considering Iran for your <strong>Liposuction</strong>, you can contact <strong>MedTourIran</strong> to get a consultation and plan your trip.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a8\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Good Candidates for Liposuction</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">You might be the right candidate for<strong> Liposuction</strong> if:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>There are fat areas in your body that are stubborn and won&rsquo;t go away no matter how much you exercise or diet</li>\n<li>Your weight is stable</li>\n<li>&nbsp;You are not using <strong>Liposuction</strong> as a weight-loss method and have realistic expectations</li>\n<li>You are within 30% of your ideal weight</li>\n<li>You have firm and elastic skin</li>\n<li>You don&rsquo;t have medical conditions that will impact the healing process</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">&nbsp;</p>\n</div>','categories/August2019/Y6lFG6Ob0fOzeclxAgXc.jpg',NULL,'Liposuction is a cosmetic surgery in which fat is removed from certain areas of the body',1,'categories/August2019/PZVCc9ednRiA1NsEmVZh.jpg'),(54,13,1,'Breast Lift','breast-lift','2019-08-04 05:50:18','2019-11-26 07:22:35','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">Breast Lift Definition</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a2\">Good Candidates for Breast Lift</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a3\">Breast Lift Alternatives (Non-Surgical Breast Lift)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a4\">Breast Lift Risks and Complications</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a5\">Breast Lift Preparations</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a6\">Breast Lift Options</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a7\">Recovery from Breast Lift</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a8\">Breast Lift Costs</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a1\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Breast Lift Definition</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Breast Lift</strong>, also known as <strong>Mastopexy</strong>, is a cosmetic procedure done to raise sagging breasts. This procedure helps women feel more confident by reshaping their breasts to have a more youthful look. Sagging breasts can be caused by aging, weight loss, or breastfeeding. The difference between a <strong>breast lift</strong> and a <strong>breast reduction</strong> is that in a <strong>breast lift surgery</strong>, only excess skin is removed. However, in breast reduction, the actual breast tissue is removed. You should consult with a plastic surgeon to decide which one is best for you, but sometimes both surgeries are done together.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a2\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Good Candidates for Breast Lift</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">A <strong>breast lift</strong> might be right for you if:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>You have sagging breasts</li>\n<li>Your nipples point downward</li>\n<li>You have uneven breasts, or one is lower than the other</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Keep in mind that if you want to get pregnant, this surgery might not be right for you because pregnancy eliminates the effect of a <strong>breast lift</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a3\" class=\"template-subtitle\"><strong>Breast Lift Alternatives</strong> (Non-Surgical Breast Lift)</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">There is a way to lift sagging breasts without having surgery. This alternative procedure uses PRP (Platelet Rich Plasma) and radiofrequency waves to lift the breasts. This method is also known as \'Vampire Breast Lift.\' Vampire Breast lift method doesn\'t need general anesthesia. Also, there is no downtime. This approach will increase breast and nipple sensitivity, reduce wrinkles, and it will lift sagging breasts without any surgery. For optimal results, a <strong>vampire breast lift</strong> is combined with microneedling or laser resurfacing.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a4\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Breast Lift Risks and Complications</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">All major surgeries have risks, and breast lift surgery is not an exception. Some of this surgery\'s risks are:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Scarring. The scars will fade over time but will not disappear completely. However, the scars can become thick and wide due to poor healing.</li>\n<li>Difficulty breastfeeding</li>\n<li>Asymmetrical breasts</li>\n<li>Changes in nipple or breast sensation</li>\n<li>Bleeding</li>\n<li>Anesthesia risks</li>\n<li>Infection</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a5\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Breast Lift Preparations</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">During your consultation, your plastic surgeon will:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Review your medical history. Your surgeon will ask about your current and past medical conditions. You should notify your surgeon if you have a family history of breast cancer.</li>\n<li>Examine your breasts. Your doctor will examine your breasts to determine the best approach for your surgery.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Talk to you about your expectations. You should talk about why you want to have this surgery and what you are hoping for as a result.</li>\n<li>Take photographs for your medical record.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Also, before the surgery, you need to stop smoking and avoid taking particular medication like aspirin (because it can increase bleeding).</p>\n<h3 id=\"a6\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Breast Lift Options</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Depending on the patient\'s condition, there are three types of <strong>breast lift</strong>:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li><strong>Periareolar incision</strong>: This approach is best for those who have large areolas and minimal breast sagging.</li>\n<li><strong>Vertical breast reduction incision</strong>: This approach is more suitable for patients with moderate sagging in their breasts.</li>\n<li><strong>Inverted-T incision: </strong>This approach, in which the maximum breast lift is obtained, is the most common one.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a7\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Recovery from Breast Lift</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">During the first few days after the surgery, you can take painkillers that are recommended by your doctor to alleviate the pain. You might feel numb for up to six weeks. Your breasts will also swell and bruise, but these symptoms will subside after about two weeks. Your surgeon might place small tubes at the incision sites to drain excess blood or fluid. Your surgeon will usually remove the tubes after a few days. If your surgeon hasn\'t used dissolvable stitches, you need to visit your doctor to have your stitches removed, usually 1-2 weeks after the surgery. Keep in mind that the results of a <strong>breast lift</strong> are not permanent because as you age, your skin becomes less elastic.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a8\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Breast Lift Costs</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">The cost of this cosmetic surgery starts from about $2100, $2900, $2300, $3000 and $3600 in India, Turkey, UK, Mexico, and Thailand, respectively. The <strong>breast lift surgery</strong> costs averagely about $3300 in European countries. In Iran, this surgery is done at the same quality, but the price of it starts from $1600.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>','categories/August2019/6bKOaOMndlkWGrzdyMqe.jpg',NULL,'Breast Lift, also known as Mastopexy, is a cosmetic procedure aiming to raise sagging breasts. This procedure helps women feel more confident by reshaping their breasts for a more youthful look. Sagging breasts can be caused by aging, weight loss, or breastfeeding. The difference between a breast lift and a breast reduction is that in a breast lift surgery only excess tissue is removed. You should with a plastic surgeon to decide which one is best for you but sometimes both surgeries are done together. ',0,'categories/August2019/QHVszdIpCSzWKBWCduqB.jpg'),(55,13,1,'plastic surgery','plastic-surgery','2019-08-04 06:07:01','2019-11-26 07:31:35','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">What is Plastic Surgery?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a2\">Reconstructive surgery</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a3\">Why Choose Iran?</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a1\" class=\"template-subtitle\">What is Plastic Surgery?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Did you know that the word &ldquo;<strong>plastic</strong>&rdquo; in <strong>plastic surgery</strong> comes from the Greek word &ldquo;<strong>plastikos</strong>&rdquo;? Plastikos means &ldquo;<strong>the art of modeling</strong>&rdquo; and has nothing to do with the plastic (synthetic material) you probably have in mind. <strong>Plastic surgery</strong> can be done for both cosmetic and aesthetic reasons or to reconstruct a part of the body.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a2\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Reconstructive Surgery<a class=\"imp\" href=\"https://medtouriran.com/en/blogs/9/what-is-reconstructive-surgery\">Read More</a></h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Reconstructive surgery</strong> aims to repair the defects and improve the functioning of your body, such as:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Tumor removal&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Hand surgery</li>\n<li>Burn surgery</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a3\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Cosmetic Surgery<a class=\"imp\" href=\"https://medtouriran.com/en/blogs/10/what-is-cosmetic-surgery\">Read More</a></h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Cosmetic surgery</strong> aims to improve the overall appearance and remove signs of aging. <strong>Cosmetic surgeries</strong> are done voluntarily. The word &ldquo;surgery&rdquo; doesn&rsquo;t necessarily mean that surgeons cut a part of the body. Botox is a good example of this type of surgery. The most popular <strong>cosmetic procedures</strong> include:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Rhinoplasty (nose job).<a class=\"imp\" href=\"https://medtouriran.com/en/procedures/43/rhinoplasty\">Read More</a></li>\n<li>Facelift (delaying the visible signs of aging)</li>\n<li>Breast enhancement<a class=\"imp\" href=\"https://medtouriran.com/en/procedures/16/breast-surgery\">Read More</a></li>\n<li>Genioplasty (chin surgery)</li>\n<li>Laser skin resurfacing</li>\n<li>Liposuction (fat removal)<a class=\"imp\" href=\"https://medtouriran.com/en/procedures/52/liposuction\">Read More</a></li>\n<li>Botox</li>\n<li>Laser hair removal</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a4\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Why Choose Iran?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">According to many people, Iran is the best country to have <strong>plastic surgery</strong> in the Middle East. Thus, travelers in the Middle East often head to Iran for liposuction, rhinoplasty, and other kinds of plastic surgery. Iran has become a reference for <strong>plastic surgery</strong> in the Middle East and attracts tourists from all over the world. It is estimated that more than 30,000 <strong>plastic surgeries</strong> are performed per year in the country. This high demand can be due to the following reasons:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li><strong>Skilled Doctors: </strong>The choice of the best plastic surgeon plays an important and crucial role in surgeries and leads to favorable results. Iranian doctors are trained in the country&rsquo;s top medical universities. Thanks to Iranian surgeon&rsquo;s unique set of skills, and the latest medical technology at world-class facilities, they perform more than 30,000 plastic surgeries per year.<a class=\"imp\" href=\"https://medtouriran.com/en/services/doctors\">More Info</a></li>\n<li><strong>Low Costs: Plastic surgery</strong> is usually not covered by insurance. As a result, the costs can be quite outrageous. One of the primary reasons to travel to Iran for surgery is that <strong>plastic surgery</strong> costs in Iran are more affordable. People can generally expect to save at least 60% when performing <strong>plastic surgery</strong> in Iran as compared to Western countries. These costs include all the travel expenses like airfares, hotel, and food during one&rsquo;s stay.</li>\n<li><strong>Low Waiting Period: </strong>The waiting times for procedures in Iran are usually non-existent. Compare this to the Western nations, for instance, in Canada. It takes a patient about four weeks to consult a specialist while in Iran the patients have immediate access to a specialist. Many people use medical tourism in Iran as an option to get procedures done faster when they are fed up with the waiting times in their native countries.</li>\n<li><strong>Privacy: </strong>Privacy is another reason to have <strong>plastic surgery</strong> away from home. Most of us do not wish to run into our neighbors while recovering. In Iran, you will be able to recuperate in peace and do some sightseeing in the city.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>','categories/August2019/F2n1zxOAqdtVlLlSquFn.jpg',NULL,'Did you know that the word “plastic” in plastic surgery comes from the Greek word “plastikos” which means “the art of modeling” and has nothing to do with the plastic (synthetic material) you probably have in mind? Plastic surgery can be done for cosmetic/aesthetic reasons or to reconstruct a part of the body. ',1,'categories/August2019/wFFYpvSgdF6w2efqBjwW.jpg'),(59,13,1,'Tummy Tuck','tummy-tuck','2019-08-31 05:59:27','2019-11-26 08:05:46','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">Abdominoplasty Definition</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a2\">Tummy Tuck Alternatives&nbsp;</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a3\">Abdominoplasty Preparations</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a4\">Abdominoplasty Procedure</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a5\">Abdominoplasty Complications and Risks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a6\">Abdominoplasty Recovery</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a7\">Why Choose Iran for Your Abdominoplasty?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a8\">Abdominoplasty Costs</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a1\" class=\"template-subtitle\"><span style=\"font-size: 18.72px;\">Abdominoplasty Definition</span></h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Abdominoplasty</strong> is a cosmetic surgery which is also known as \'<strong>Tummy Tuck</strong>.\' This surgery aims to make the abdomen thinner and firmer. Pregnancy or a major weight loss can cause sagging tissues, and having a <strong>Tummy Tuck</strong> remove the issue. <strong>Abdominoplasty</strong> reduces sagging abdomens by removing excess fat and skin or tightening the muscles in the area. It is important to keep in mind that<strong> Tummy Tuck</strong> should not be considered as an alternative to weight loss. <strong>Abdominoplasty</strong> and <strong>Liposuction</strong> can be done together to improve the apearance of the abdomen.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a2\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Tummy Tuck Alternatives&nbsp;</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">If you are suffering from sagging skin in your abdomen but do not want to have surgery, there is an alternative. This alternative is called \'<strong>Thermalipo</strong>\' which has a more comfortable recovery and shorter treatment time. This method uses <strong>Liposuction</strong> and Thermage Radiofrequency Skin Tightening (a non-invasive treatment for aging and loose skin). After the <strong>Liposuction</strong>, the Thermage device is used to tighten the skin by using radiofrequency energy to stimulate collagen growth. Beside the abdomen, the <strong>Thermalipo</strong> can be used for other areas as well.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a3\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Abdominoplasty Preparations</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Procedure you need to follow before your surgery:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Stop smoking because it slows down the healing process and increases the risk of infection</li>\n<li>Reach your ideal weight but don\'t try an extreme diet and eat complete meals</li>\n<li>Discuss your medical history with your surgeon</li>\n<li>Talk about your expectations</li>\n<li>Arrange for someone from <strong>MedTourIran</strong> to take you home and stay with you for a couple of days after the surgery</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a4\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Abdominoplasty Procedure</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">This procedure usually takes 1-5 hours, and it\'s performed under general anesthesia which means you will be unconscious during the operation. Depending on the patient\'s condition, the surgeon can perform the surgery in two different ways:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li><strong>Complete Abdominoplasty</strong>. If your surgeon chooses this method, he will make an incision on the abdomen from hipbone to hipbone, which will move your belly button.&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Mini Abdominoplasty,</strong> or <strong>Partial Abdominoplasty</strong>. This method is less invasive and more suitable for those who have a small amount of excess fat or if their fat deposits are located below the belly button. During the<strong> Mini Abdominoplasty</strong>, the surgeon will make incisions under the belly button and will not move it.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a5\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Abdominoplasty Complications and Risks</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Just like any other surgery, <strong>Abdominoplasty</strong> carries risks such as:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Infection</li>\n<li>Anesthesia risks</li>\n<li>Bleeding</li>\n<li>Blood cloths</li>\n<li>Seroma</li>\n<li>Hematoma</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Having diabetes, heart, or liver conditions makes it more likely for complications to happen. The scars of this surgery will fade over time but will not disappear completely.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a6\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Abdominoplasty Recovery</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">After the surgery, you will experience pain, soreness, and swelling during the first few days. Your doctor will probably prescribe painkillers to deal with pain. The soreness will subside after a few weeks or months. Bruising is also a possibility. You must limit your activities for at least six weeks. Diet and exercise regularly to maintain the results of your <strong>Abdominoplasty.</strong></p>\n<h3 id=\"a7\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Why Choose Iran for Your Abdominoplasty?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">You might wonder if it\'s worth traveling to another country for surgery? It only makes sense if you have to pay less for the same quality of services. In Iran, you can get the same quality of services if not more, at lower and more affordable prices. Iranian surgeons are well-educated and experienced. The clinics and hospitals in Iran are fully equipped and advanced, so you have to worry about anything. The hospitable and kind people of Iran, its historical and cultural attractions, and delicious cuisine are just some of the many things you\'ll miss if you don\'t choose Iran. However, if you have selected Iran as your destination, feel free to contact <strong>MedTourIran</strong> and get a consultation and plan your trip.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a8\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Abdominoplasty Costs</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Abdominoplasty</strong> averagely costs about&nbsp;<strong>$</strong><strong>2500</strong>&nbsp;in Iran. But the same surgery will cost you around&nbsp;<strong>$</strong><strong>3000</strong> in India. The cost of this surgery ranges from <strong>$</strong><strong>4000</strong>&nbsp;to&nbsp;<strong>$</strong><strong>15000</strong>&nbsp;in European countries, and about&nbsp;<strong>$</strong><strong>6000</strong>, and&nbsp;<strong>$</strong><strong>6200</strong>&nbsp;in Thailand and Mexico respectively.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>','categories/August2019/hqEZAlKjGmkm9nodsU42.jpg',NULL,'Abdominoplasty is a cosmetic surgery also known as ‘Tummy Tuck’. This surgery is aimed to make the abdomen thinner and firmer. Pregnancy or a major weight loss cause loose and sagging tissues, and having a tummy tuck can solve the issue. Abdominoplasty reduces sagging abdomens by removing excess fat and skin, or tightening the muscles in the area. It is important to keep in mind that tummy tuck should not be considered as an alternative to weight loss. Abdominoplasty and Liposuction can be done together to improve the look of the abdomen. ',0,'categories/August2019/sBqxzSL8yhN3eZw0k9KQ.jpg'),(61,12,1,'Male Fertility','male-fertility','2019-08-31 06:15:56','2019-11-25 11:06:44','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">What is Infertility in Men?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a2\">Varicocele</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a3\">Common Causes of Infertility</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a4\">Infertility Treatment</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a5\">Why Iran?</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a1\" class=\"template-subtitle\">What is Infertility in Men?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Male infertility refers to the weakness in Male reproductive system and to those factors and problems associated with it. Male infertility can have many different causes, such as:</p>\n<h3 class=\"template-subtitle\">Varicocele</h3>\n<h3 id=\"a2\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Infertility symptoms</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">If you are diagnosed with Infertility (unable to conceive a child), you can get treatment. But first let&rsquo;s take a look at some of the symptoms that can help you to seek help earlier:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li><strong>Irregular menstrual periods :&nbsp;</strong>One of the signs which shows that a woman ovulates regularly is having regular menstrual periods (every 21 to 35 days). Ovulation of the egg is necessary for pregnancy. Therefore, if you&rsquo;re trying to conceive a baby and you have irregular menstrual cycles, do not wait until the 12th month and take action and see a doctor to find out the problem.</li>\n<li><strong>Women over 35 :&nbsp;</strong>As women age, they face decreasing in the number of eggs and it is less likely for an egg to be genetically normal. Accordingly, if a couple has been trying to have a baby for 6 months or more and the woman is over 35 years old, they&rsquo;d better be evaluated for infertility.</li>\n<li><strong>&nbsp;A history of sexually transmitted diseases :&nbsp;</strong>A sperm must cross the tubes in order to reach the ovulated egg and fertilize it. Therefore, open tubes are essential to get pregnant naturally. Sexually transmitted diseases such as gonorrhea, can damage fallopian tubes and prevent a proper conception. That is why if the woman has a history of pelvic infection, should get an immediate evaluation if the couple intends to conceive a child.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a3\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Common Causes of Infertility</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Delaying childbirth:</strong> As discussed previously, the number of eggs will diminish as a woman ages. A woman beyond the age of 45 is unlikely to get pregnant.</li>\n<li><strong>Endometrial polyps:</strong> Endometrial polyps can arise from the inner lining of the uterus and can decrease fertility. In some cases, if the doctor simply removes the polyp, your infertility will be solved.</li>\n<li><strong>&nbsp;Male factor infertility:</strong> If the abnormality of semen is confirmed, the guy should visit a reproductive urologist to get proper treatment.</li>\n<li><strong>Uterine fibroids:</strong> Fibroids are very common among women and have 3 types. Submucosal fibroids are the type that can reduce the chance of pregnancy and need to be treated so that the couple can have a baby.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a4\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Infertility Treatment</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Couples need to educate themselves about the symptoms of infertility so that they can recognize when to seek help. Aside from that, your doctor can suggest special treatments to aid conceiving a baby:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li><strong>Medications:</strong> In order to stimulate egg development and ovulation, your doctor may prescribe special pills or injections. You should use them as you&rsquo;re instructed to enhance the chance of conceiving a baby.</li>\n<li><strong>Insemination:</strong> Insemination is a method in which they take the sperm and prepare it for placement into the uterine cavity. In this case, there is a higher opportunity for the sperm to get closer to the ovulated egg. The man needs to be checked for sperm abnormality, otherwise, the sperm cannot swim and fertilize the egg.&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>In Vitro Fertilization:</strong> IVF means &ldquo;outside the body&rdquo; and the reason is that in this process, they collect eggs and fertilize them by sperm outside the body, in the laboratory. They check the eggs again after about 40 hours and if they are fertilized, they will be put back in the woman\'s uterus.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a5\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Why Iran?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Aside from <strong>affordable prices</strong> for infertility treatment in Iran (compared to other countries), there are a number of other reasons that you&rsquo;d better consider visiting this country to find the best treatment awaiting you:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Advanced treatment for infertility</li>\n<li>Knowledgeable and experienced specialists</li>\n<li>Well-equipped hospitals and laboratories</li>\n<li>Beautiful attractions to visit while you are in the city</li>\n</ul>\n</div>','categories/September2019/X5zA7KdrHpYpb80UOwnU.jpg',NULL,'Male infertility refers to weakness in Male reproductive system and to those factors and problems associated with that. Male infertility can have many different causes',0,'categories/September2019/rzSJsPqrVNs1yhqwPm0Y.jpg'),(62,13,1,'Breast Reduction','breast-reduction','2019-08-04 05:50:18','2019-11-26 08:17:26','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">What is Breast Reduction Surgery?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a2\">Why Choose Iran for Breast Reduction?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a3\">Why Choose MedTourIran?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a4\">Breast Reduction Risks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a5\">Breast Reduction Preparations</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a6\">Recovery from Breast Reduction Surgery</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a7\">Non-Surgical Breast Reduction Surgery</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a8\">Breast Reduction Surgery Costs</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a1\" class=\"template-subtitle\">&nbsp;What is Breast Reduction Surgery?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Breast reduction surgery</strong> or <strong>reduction mammoplasty</strong> is a procedure aimed to reduce the size of the breasts by removing excess fat, tissue, and skin. Sometimes, extremely large breasts will cause women to lose confidence and even cause neck and back pain and other physical symptoms. These factors may be why some consider <strong>Breast reduction surgery</strong>. Even men suffering from gynecomastia can get this surgery. So <strong>Breast reduction surgery</strong> isn\'t just a cosmetic surgery and can have medical purposes as well. To get the most out of a <strong>Breast reduction surgery,</strong> and have a natural outcome, your BMI must not be higher than 35. <strong>Breast reduction surgery</strong> usually includes a<strong> Breast Lift</strong> too.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a2\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Why Choose Iran for Breast Reduction Surgery?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">You may wonder if it\'s reasonable to travel to another country for plastic surgery? It only makes sense if the surgery is performed with the same quality but at a lower price. The surgeons in Iran are well educated, highly experienced, and the success rate of plastic surgeries in Iran is very high. Because not only Iran has very top surgeons but also modern clinic and hospitals. Due to economic factors, the costs of surgeries in Iran are more affordable and lower than other countries such as the UK, USA, Mexico, and Canada. The rich culture of Iran, its history, hospitable people, and excellent cuisine also make Iran an excellent tourism destination. So, Iran is one of the best choices for medical tourism.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a3\" class=\"template-subtitle\"><span style=\"font-size: 18.72px;\">Why Choose MedTourIran?</span></h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>MedTourIran</strong> has been established in Iran as the biggest center offering medical, surgery, and cosmetic services. This company provides high-quality services at affordable prices using qualified medical experts, advanced clinics, and hospitals. Our main goal&nbsp;is to prevent dealers who despite receiving high rates, link people to unreliable and incompetent centers.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a4\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Breast Reduction Surgery Risks</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">As with any other major surgery, <strong>Breast reduction</strong> also carries risks such as:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Bleeding</li>\n<li>Infection</li>\n<li>Anesthesia risks</li>\n<li>Bruising or scarring</li>\n<li>Difficulty or not being able to breastfeed</li>\n<li>Asymmetrical breast</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a5\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Breast Reduction Surgery Preparations</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Before having<strong> Breast reduction surgery,</strong> there are a few things you must do:</p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Your surgeon will evaluate your overall health and medical history</li>\n<li class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Your surgeon will also walk you through the procedure and discuss the risks and the benefits of <strong>breast reduction</strong></li>\n<li class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Your breast will be examined, measured, and photographed for medical record</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Before <strong>Breast reduction surgery</strong>, you should stop smoking and avoid taking aspirin because it may increase bleeding. You may be asked to take various lab tests. If you are not staying at the hospital, you should arrange for someone to take you home and stay with you for at least one night.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a6\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Recovery from Breast Reduction Surgery</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">After the surgery, your surgeon will cover your breasts with bandages, and prescribe painkillers and antibiotics to reduce the risk of infection. For the first few days, your breasts will probably feel sensitive and might swell and bruise. It usually takes about 2-6 weeks to recover from <strong>Breast reduction surgery,</strong> and you need to limit your physical activity for the first 2-4 weeks. You should rest as much as possible, watch TV or read a good book. The scars will fade over time but won\'t completely disappear. You may experience some temporary side effects during the first few months like numbness.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a7\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Non-Surgical Breast Reduction Surgery</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">You can reduce the size of your breasts by one or two cup sizes using <strong>Power-Assisted Liposuction</strong> (PAL). This approach is less invasive and safer than surgery and can be very helpful. <strong>Non-surgical Breast Reduction</strong> is usually performed under general anesthesia. This approach can make your breast smaller and lighter without changing their natural shape, and most patients can return to their daily activities the following day.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a8\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Breast Reduction Surgery Costs</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">The price of<strong> Breast reduction</strong> in Iran starts from $800, but this surgery\'s price in India starts from $2500. <strong>Breast reduction surgery</strong> averagely costs around $3700, $5600, and $8100 in Turkey, USA, and the UK, respectively. Also, the costs range from about $1570 in Bulgaria to $5000 in Spain. Considering the prices and the quality of the services offered in Iran, this country can be the best option for this surgery and medical tourism in general.</p>\n</div>','categories/September2019/3EkEPuXueIDOiHM1gWIb.jpg',NULL,'Breast reduction surgery or reduction mammoplasty is a procedure aimed to reduce the size of the breasts by removing excess fat, tissue, and skin. Sometimes, extremely large breast will cause women to lose confidence and even cause neck and back pain and other physical symptoms. These factors may be why some consider Breast reduction surgery. Even men suffering from gynecomastia can get this surgery. So Breast reduction surgery isn’t just a cosmetic surgery and can have medical purposes. To get the most out of a Breast reduction surgery and have a natural outcome, your BMI must not be higher than 35. Breast reduction surgery usually includes a Breast Lift too.',0,'categories/September2019/jcks6NT83zxj1pUheq8t.jpg');
