INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (9,2,34,'What is Reconstructive Surgery?','What is Reconstructive Surgery?','Reconstructive surgery is usually covered by your health insurance and includes various operations such as hand or foot surgery, skin cancer removal, burn care','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">What is Reconstructive Surgery?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a2\">Dental health</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a3\">Eye care</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a4\">Infertility treatment</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a5\">Why Iran?</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a1\" class=\"template-subtitle\">What is Reconstructive Surgery?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Reconstructive surgery is a type of plastic surgery in which patients&rsquo; intention to do the operation has <strong>medical</strong> reasons. The main purpose of this procedure is to correct the defects of your body or get treatment for a disease, while the goal in Cosmetic Surgery is to look better which we discussed in another article. Reconstructive surgery is usually covered by your health insurance and includes various operations such as hand or foot surgery, skin cancer removal, burn care in addition to the following treatments:</p>\n<h3 id=\"a2\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Dental health</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Dental health has a huge impact on your overall well-being and you need to take oral hygiene habits seriously; otherwise, its consequence will be costly and might lead to diseases that put your health in danger. The easiest way to take care of your teeth is to brush and floss them regularly. There are also a number of other treatments such as fillings and implants that can help you deal with oral problems.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a3\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Eye care</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Dental health has a huge impact on your overall well-being and you need to take oral hygiene habits seriously; otherwise, its consequence will be costly and might lead to diseases that put your health in danger. The easiest way to take care of your teeth is to brush and floss them regularly. There are also a number of other treatments such as fillings and implants that can help you deal with oral problems.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a4\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Infertility treatment</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Dental health has a huge impact on your overall well-being and you need to take oral hygiene habits seriously; otherwise, its consequence will be costly and might lead to diseases that put your health in danger. The easiest way to take care of your teeth is to brush and floss them regularly. There are also a number of other treatments such as fillings and implants that can help you deal with oral problems.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a5\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Why Iran?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Aside from visiting historical sites and top tourist attractions in Iran, choosing this country for doing your reconstructive surgery has the following benefits:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>You don&rsquo;t need to worry about the quality of the service you get.</li>\n<li>You&rsquo;ll get treated by experienced and knowledgeable surgeons.</li>\n<li>All the medical services are available at a low cost compared to other western countries.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>','posts/August2019/9Fx8RpQerY2yx3Do3jPH.jpg','what-is-reconstructive-surgery','Reconstructive surgery is usually covered by your health insurance and includes various operations such as hand or foot surgery, skin cancer removal, burn ','medtouriran ,medical tourism,iran tourism,Reconstructive surgery','PUBLISHED',0,'2019-08-14 03:23:24','2019-09-08 14:04:04','posts/September2019/LbVnZfaf0uHXEo0aQSix.jpg'),(10,2,12,'What is Cosmetic Surgery?','what is cosmetic surgery','Cosmetic surgery is a popular plastic surgery which its main goal is to improve your appearance and give you confidence and usually it is not covered by health insurance. ','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">What is Cosmetic Surgery?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a2\">Why Iran?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a3\">Types of Cosmetic Surgery</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a1\" class=\"template-subtitle\">What is Cosmetic Surgery?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Cosmetic surgery is a popular plastic surgery which its main goal is to improve your appearance and give you confidence and usually it is not covered by health insurance. This is not the case in reconstructive surgery that its main focus is on medical purposes and improves the function of a part of your body. We will address that issue in another article. Let&rsquo;s get to cosmetic surgery for now.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a2\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Why Iran?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Cosmetic surgery deals with changing your appearance and the main goal is to make it better. Therefore, it is important to choose the right surgeon to do the operation. Iran is one of the best medical tourism countries in the Middle East due to the following reasons:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>The number of patients that Iranian surgeons deal with every day has given them enough experience</li>\n<li>As a result, the success rate of cosmetic surgery is quite high in Iran</li>\n<li>The advanced pieces of equipment of hospitals in Iran and the low cost of treatments are another reason to choose Iran for your surgery</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a3\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Types of Cosmetic Surgery</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Different types of cosmetic surgery are available for patients such as breast surgery (reduction, lift, and enlargement), eyelid surgery, ear surgery, chin surgery, brow lift, facelift, laser treatment and liposuction (fat removal). Three cosmetic surgeries are more common among people; thus we will take a quick look at each one of them:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Plastic surgery</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Plastic surgery includes both cosmetic and medical surgery. The difference between a plastic surgeon and a cosmetic surgeon is related to their training length.</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Rhinoplasty</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Nose job or rhinoplasty has recently become very popular among people all around the world and can be done to give patients a better look or to improve breathing.&nbsp;</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Hair transplantation</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Hair transplant attracts people with hair loss and helps them to grow hair on the balding parts of their body. This procedure is not gender-specific and can provide assistance to women dealing with thinning hair as well.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>','posts/September2019/hglcMBfKhnYhyD6wvKWX.jpg','what-is-cosmetic-surgery','Cosmetic surgery is a popular plastic surgery which its main goal is to improve your appearance and give you confidence and usually it is not covered by health insurance. This is not the case in reconstructive surgery that its main focus is on medical purposes and improves the function of a part of your body. We will address that issue in another article. Let’s get to cosmetic surgery for now.','medtouriran ,medical tourism,iran tourism,cosmetic surgery','PUBLISHED',0,'2019-08-14 03:24:37','2019-09-03 03:29:04','posts/September2019/l5VGeWq3X4iljyZaNFxQ.jpg'),(11,2,12,'What is Medical Tourism?','Medical Tourism in Iran,medtouriran,Iran’s Medical Tourism Services','In short Medical Tourism is using world class services and facilities at low and unbelievable prices.','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">What is Medical Tourism?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a2\">Medical Tourism in Iran</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a3\">Why Choose Iran for Medical Tourism? </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a4\">Iran&rsquo;s Medical Tourism Services</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a5\">Iran&rsquo;s Leading Medical Tourism Cities</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a1\" class=\"template-subtitle\">What is Medical Tourism?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\"><strong>Medical Tourism</strong> which is sometimes referred to as &ldquo;Health Tourism&rdquo; has various definitions. According to The World Tourism Organization Medical Tourism is &lsquo;using services which lead to a boost in a person&rsquo;s health or morale (with the help of medical techniques, the weather, etc.) which happens away from that person&rsquo;s home&rsquo;. In short <strong>Medical Tourism</strong> is using world class services and facilities at low and unbelievable prices.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a2\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Medical Tourism in Iran</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">In Iran, Medical Tourism trustees include: Cultural Heritage, Handicrafts and Tourism Organization of Iran (ICHTO), Ministry of Health and Medical Education, Ministry of Foreign Affairs (MFA). Compared to other countries the development and expansion of Medical Tourism requires more cooperation. Medical tourists are usually from countries like Azerbaijan Republic, Iraq, Turkmenistan, Kuwait, Syria, Lebanon, Turkey, and Bahrain.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a3\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Why Choose Iran for <strong>Medical Tourism</strong>?</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Costs</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Compared to other countries like the US and European countries, Iran&rsquo;s most important advantage in Medical Tourism are the costs. Currently India is a forerunner in offering the cheapest services but with Iran entering the competition and considering its tourism potential, more historical attractions, and its very warm-hearted people, Iran has the ability to attract more tourists than India.</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Hydrotherapy</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<p>Hydrotherapy is another one of Iran&rsquo;s attraction and it is very important in <strong>Medical Tourism</strong>. According to the statistics, about 45 million tourists use hydrotherapy for their treatment. And since Iran has more than a thousand known mineral water springs, it can be a very good choice for this purpose.</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Sludge therapy</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<p>Iran can also attract tourists for sludge therapy since it has the facilities for it like Taftan mountain hillsides, and Urmia lake&rsquo;s beaches.</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Salt therapy</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<p>Salt therapy and cave therapy have recently gained the interest of many international tourists and because Iran contains many salt domes it can become a center for salt therapy.</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Traditional medicine</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<p>Recently, many have been interested is Persian traditional medicine and even some are studying it. according to&nbsp; (a medical historian), traditional medicine existed in Iran before it existed in Greece. And it was Persians who taught Greeks the principles of what they call Greek medicine.</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Climate</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<p>Iran&rsquo;s resorts in Deylaman (Gilan), Javaher deh (Mazandaran) or Shandiz are famous and known all around the world.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a4\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Iran&rsquo;s Medical Tourism Services</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Most people travel to Iran for one of the following purposes:</p>\n<ul class=\"template-ul\">\n<li>Infertility</li>\n<li>Dental care</li>\n<li>Heart, Eye, and plastic surgeries</li>\n<li>Cancer related illnesses</li>\n<li>Cancer related illnesses</li>\n<li>Tourism in healing waters</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a5\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Iran&rsquo;s Leading Medical Tourism Cities</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://medtouriran.com/en/destinations/1/tehran\">Tehran</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Tehran which is Iran&rsquo;s capital enjoys well-known medical specialists and terrific facilities in its hospitals and clinics. Being close to Alborz mountain&rsquo;s hillside has made Tehran&rsquo;s weather really nice. While using medical services, you can also spend time sightseeing.<a class=\"imp\" href=\"https://medtouriran.com/en/destinations/1/tehran\">read more</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://medtouriran.com/en/destinations/2/mashhad\">Mashhad</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Mashhad is a religious city with fine medical equipment and facilities. Imam Reza&rsquo;s shrine, specialized and experienced clinics and hospitals for beauty and medical services have made this city one of the first choices for <strong>Medical Tourism</strong>.<a class=\"imp\" href=\"https://medtouriran.com/en/destinations/2/mashhad\">read more</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://medtouriran.com/en/destinations/3/shiraz\">Shiraz</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Shiraz is one of the destinations for Medical Tourism due to its renowned doctors, high quality treatment centers, and nice weather. Shiraz hosts many tourists from Iraq because it is a religious city and close to this country.<a class=\"imp\" href=\"https://medtouriran.com/en/destinations/3/shiraz\">read more</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Yazd</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Yazd is a historical city and has many historical attractions and is among the best cities for <strong>Medical Tourism</strong>. The presence of 545 specialized doctors, 915 general practitioners, 300 dentists, and 15 hospitals have made Yazd a destination for many tourists. This city is better known for infertility and cardiology treatments, because Yazd&rsquo;s infertility center is Iran and middle east&rsquo;s first infertility treatment center and many travel to Yazd from other countries to come to this center.</p>\n</div>','posts/August2019/2JehglFgPgqX4q7LYnif.jpg','what-is-medical-tourism','In Iran, Medical Tourism trustees include: Cultural Heritage, Handicrafts and Tourism Organization of Iran (ICHTO), Ministry of Health and Medical Education, Ministry of Foreign Affairs (MFA). Compared to other countries the development and expansion of Medical Tourism requires more cooperation. Medical tourists are usually from countries like Azerbaijan Republic, Iraq, Turkmenistan, Kuwait, Syria, Lebanon, Turkey, and Bahrain. ','Medical Tourism in Iran,unbelievable prices,Iran’s Medical Tourism Services','PUBLISHED',0,'2019-08-23 18:56:53','2019-10-17 18:08:49','posts/August2019/1d79N8ThXrMwKx4Eiinb.jpg'),(12,2,12,'All Types Of Eye Diseases And Their Treatment','','','<div id=\"template-content\" class=\"mceTmpl\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#a1\">The eye</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a2\">Eye and eye disease</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a3\">What are the eye parts? </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a4\">Types of eye diseases and their treatment</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a5\">Most common eyes disease</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a6\">Glaucoma or Glaucoma Water Eye Disease and its treatment</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a7\">Treatment of Glaucoma</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a8\">Cataract or White water</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a9\">Treatment of Cataract</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a10\">Macular Degeneration</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a11\">Treatment of Macular Degeneration</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a12\">Retinal Detachment</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a13\">Treatment of Retinal Detachment</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a14\">Conjunctivitis</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a15\">Conjunctivitis treatment</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a16\">Eye Disease Treatment in Iran and MedTourIran Company</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#a17\">Some eye surgery prices in MedTourIran</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"a1\" class=\"template-subtitle\">The eye</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">What&rsquo;s the eye? What&rsquo;s its function? What&rsquo;s eye disease? What are the most common eye diseases?&nbsp; Is eye surgery treatment performed in Iran?</p>\n<h3 id=\"a2\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Eye and eye disease</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">The eye is the embodiment of beauty and a means of looking. It is a precious part that humans possess. Some people do medical surgery for the eye while other seek the Cosmetic eye surgery. In this regard, we are going to mention the most common eye diseases and explain their treatment. The eye is likely to be affected with various diseases so we have to protect it because of its importance.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a3\" class=\"template-subtitle\">What are the eye parts?</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">At the beginning, we touch on the components of the eye to become more familiar with it. The eye is composed of The Cornea ( a transparent tissue in the middle of the eye and its function is to collect light and focus it on the Retina) Iris (a membrane that its condition changes according to the status of vision and it is influential in the color of the eye) Pupil (a gap in the center of the iris from which light passes) Lens ( collects the light and sends it to the Retina) Retina (This part takes the collected light and replaces it with nerve signals) Macula (its function is to see small details and the quality of vision placed at the center of the Retina) Optic nerve ( the means of communication between the Retina and the visual center inside the brain) and Eye Fluid ( a transparent fluid that fills the eye cavity).&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a4\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Types of eye diseases and their treatment</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Indeed, the eye is affected by various diseases and these diseases vary in terms of the area of the defect and its treatment. In this section we will mention the eye diseases and then we explain some of the common eye diseases and their treatments.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a5\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Most common eye Disease</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Glaucoma or Glaucoma water, Cataract, Macular Degeneration, Retinal Detachment, Conjunctivitis, Short-sightedness or Myopia, Diabetic Retinopathy, Retinitis Pigmentosa, Tolosa Hunt Syndrome Papillary Edema of the Optic Nerve, Macular Degeneration, Bardet Syndrome, Biddle and Cataract, Rite of the Eye, Color blindness, Amblyopia or Lazy Eye, Trachoma, Uveitis, Blepharospasm, Eyes Dehydration, Eyes sore, Endophthalmitis and Visual Atrophy, Retinal Artery Blockage, Eyelid Inflammation, Retinoblastoma, Keratitis, Primary Congenital Glaucoma, Open-angle Glaucoma, Narrow-angle glaucoma and Separate Vitreous Glaucoma.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a9\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Eye disease</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Glaucoma or Glaucoma water, Cataract, Macular Degeneration, Retinal Detachment, Conjunctivitis, Short-sightedness or Myopia, Diabetic Retinopathy, Retinitis Pigmentosa, Tolosa Hunt Syndrome Papillary Edema of the Optic Nerve, Macular Degeneration, Bardet Syndrome, Biddle and Cataract, Rite of the Eye, Color blindness, Amblyopia or Lazy Eye, Trachoma, Uveitis, Blepharospasm, Eyes Dehydration, Eyes sore, Endophthalmitis and Visual Atrophy, Retinal Artery Blockage, Eyelid Inflammation, Retinoblastoma, Keratitis, Primary Congenital Glaucoma, Open-angle Glaucoma, Narrow-angle glaucoma and Separate Vitreous Glaucoma ,etc.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a10\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Glaucoma or Glaucoma Water Eye Disease and its treatment</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Glaucoma is the most common and serious eye disease, which leads to increasingly high vision loss. The optic nerve is a section affected by glaucoma which raises internal intraocular pressure and leads to vision loss. This kind of eye disease is not accompanied by special symptoms but could be treated immediately after its discovery. It has two different types: open-angle and closed-angle glaucoma. Characteristics of the first type is that it is rife and common and the second type are severe pain as well as a sudden condition which causes vision loss.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a11\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Treatment of Glaucoma</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">It is not possible to prescribe a definite treatment for this disease but it is possible for the patient to resort to the usage of some eye drops or laser. However, full and successful treatment could be reached by early diagnosis of Glaucoma and through surgery.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a12\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Cataract or White water</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">When does a person have Cataract?&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">A person suffers from this disease when he is hit by a severe blow in his eye and when he suffers from diabetes or takes too much Cortisone. As a result, the eye lens gets affected with this disease and its color changes from transparent to dark and dusky or white and this replacement gradually continues till it is completely replaced to dark.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a13\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Treatment of Cataract</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">When cataract is diagnosed by the doctor, he recommends the patient to use sunglasses and avoid direct looking at any natural or artificial bright light, and when the person is not recovered, surgery operation is done to replace the dark lens with a new lens.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a14\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Macular Degeneration</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">This is the part that cares about the quality of the sight and seeing the small details. The elderly people suffer from this disease that is why they are considered a group with a weak central eyesight. When they look around, they can see everything that exists round them, but they cannot see it clearly.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a15\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Treatment of Macular Degeneration</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Although there are different treatments for this disease, there is no comprehensive and satisfactory treatment that could be recommended, however, some of the treatments are: laser, some antioxidant drugs, zinc and eye injection.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a16\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Retinal Detachment</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">As the name indicates, it is the case of the retinal detachment from the eye wall. When the retina moves, it is transferred from its place and is filled with liquid inside the eye cavity, this leads to the separation of the retina from the wall of the eye, but what is the reason for this movement and transfer? This movement takes place under severe collision or crack and aperture.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a17\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Treatment of Retinal Detachment</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Surgery operation is the treatment of retinal detachment and in this operation the Retina is reinstalled. We can say that this process has been successful most of the time or always and the patient gets healthy after the operation.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a18\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Conjunctivitis</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">In this disease, a person is affected with inflammation of the conjunctiva and transparent membrane and its redness. This type of disease appears because of eye infection via bacteria or virus or because of sensitivity in the eye and exposure to dust or what harms the eye.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a19\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Conjunctivitis treatment</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Treatments differ when we talk about the treatment of conjunctivitis because of the different factors in creating this disease. When the eye is infected with virus only antiseptic drops and when the eye is infected with bacteria antibiotic drops are used.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a19\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Uveitis</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Uveitis (anterior uveitis) is one of the most serious and the rarest eye diseases. This inflammation is a type of uveitis and is caused by an inflammation of the blood vessels that carry oxygen and food to the eye cells.&nbsp; This is why they play a prominent role in the quality of vision and eye functions. Causes of eye infection with this disease are bacteria, virus or a genetic factor.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a19\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Uveitis Treatment</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">There are different treatments for anterior uveitis, but the best treatment is the early treatment which must be done before the disease develops in the eye.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"a19\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Eye Disease Treatment in Iran and MedTourIran Company</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Is eye surgery performed in Iran? Are there specialist doctors in Iran? How much is the price of eye surgery?&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Yes, every operation related to the treatment of eye diseases is carried out in Iran. Specialized clinics and advanced hospitals in Iran perform surgery to treat all types of eye diseases. Iran utilizes the expertise of doctors who have studied at the best universities in the world and Iran.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">MedtourIran company provides you with the best services and the best doctors to diagnose and treat eye diseases and can attend in its medical centers (some hospitals and clinics) in Tehran and Mashhad and Shiraz and follow up your health.</p>\n<h3 id=\"a19\" class=\"template-subtitle\">Some eye surgery prices in MedtorIran</h3>\n<p class=\"paragraph-medium paragraph-black template-p\">Cataract surgery cost&nbsp; with lens implant in Tehran is 1265 $ for both eyes.</p>\n<p class